{title: Broken Down Merry Go Round}
{artist: Slim Whitman}
{composer: Written by Arthur Herbert and Fred Stryker}

[G]You said that you loved me but it wasn't [D7]long till I found
That you had me riding a broken down [G]merry go round
Sweet [D7]kisses you [G]gave me but soon it was [D7]all over town
That you had me riding a broken down [G]merry go round
You [C]told me that you would [G]always be near
[D7]Love me my dear through [G]sorrow and tears
But [C]all I have left is a [G]brass souvenir
[Am]Instead of a ring made of [D7]gold
My [G]poor heart is breaking you've made me a [D7]fool and a clown
For you had me riding a broken down [G]merry go round
Repeat #2,3
[D7]Yes you had me riding a broken down merry go [G]round